  <Docs>
    <summary>The ClrBuffer allocates the memory using the .NET VM.</summary>
    <remarks>The byte array which is used by the clr buffer is pinned down, in order for the guarantee interop safety with the sundown library.

<para>
Growing the buffer is slower than compared to the NativeBuffer, but if no buffer growing is needed, the ClrBuffer will achieve superior performance.
</para>

<para>
Doesn't work without a modified sundown version.
</para></remarks>
  </Docs>
